post_text:
Sweeny ISD is excited to be able to take advantage of a program provided by the federal government to help ensure that the children in our community continue to receive meals during the COVID-19 pandemic.

Beginning Monday September 14, all children in Sweeny will be able to receive breakfast and lunch at no cost each and every school day. This will be available for students learning in person, students learning virtually, and children (ages 0-18) not currently enrolled in school. This program is currently set to end December 18, 2020. Meals will continue to be available via delivery and curbside pick-up every Tuesday and Friday.

To receive a delivery or to pick-up a meal you must place a pre-order. For more information and to place your order please visit: http://sweenyisd.org/departments/child_nutrition

post_text: Elementary supply and medication drop-off - Friday, September 11th from 3:00 pm - 6:00 pm.
shared_text:
Sweeny Elementary School
September 8 at 12:51 PM ·

The elementary is hosting a supply and medication drop off drive-through Friday, September 11th from 3:00-6:00. Staff members will take the supplies to your child's homeroom teacher. This is an OPTIONAL supply drop-off for parents who feel that their child may have difficulty carrying all of their supplies in their backpacks on the first day of school.

Please remember that parents and guardians will not be allowed to walk their child/ren to their classroom/s.

Nurses will also be on hand to collect medication. For the health and safety of our students and staff, Sweeny ISD nurses will only be accepting prescription medication and over the counter medication with a doctor's note for a documented medical condition for the 2020-21 school year. Over the counter medication will not be given to a student who has symptoms similar to COVID-19.

Please contact the school nurse for any questions or concerns.

post_text:
Friday Night Football is back! The 2020 season will look a little different this year due to COVID-19. We have procedures in place from TEA and UIL to help us ensure a safe environment for all spectators.

1. Everyone must have a ticket to enter the stadium on game day. Tickets are limited (50% capacity). The cost of tickets are $6.00 for adults and $3.00 for students. Anyone with a pass will need to get a ticket from the ticket booth.

2. General admission seats will sit in the first two sections of the stadium. Reserved seats with be seated in the middle and top of the fourth section of the stadium. The Belles and Band will have designated seating. Please do not sit in rows marked with the red X and follow social distancing guidelines.

3. Fans are required to wear face coverings.

4. The concession stand and restrooms will be available. Please follow social distancing guidelines while waiting in line.

5. Gates will open at 6:30 pm

post_text:
As of the 10:30 advisory from the National Weather Service and Brazoria County, Sweeny ISD has determined that all virtual instruction will be cancelled for Wednesday, August 26th and Thursday, August 27th in order to give our families and faculty time to prepare for a possible landfall of Hurricane Laura.

At this time, all extracurricular activities will be cancelled and district facilities will be closed on Wednesday, August 26th. We will continue to monitor the landfall of Laura and will make a decision regarding extracurricular activities for Thursday and virtual learning on Friday, August 28th as soon as we can.

Know that the safety of our families, students, and staff is our main priority. Please check for updates on all social media outlets as well as our website. Please be safe! #WeAreSweeny Sweeny High School Sweeny Elementary School Sweeny Junior High

Sweeny ISD will host our Back to (Virtual) School drive-through event at Sweeny High School on Friday, August 14th from 8:00 am to 12:00 pm. This will be your last opportunity to pick-up, drop-off, or exchange essential technology items (iPads and Hotspots) prior to the first day of Virtual Learning.

Calculators will also be available for pick up on Friday.

JH - 7th grade honors math students and all 8th grade students will pick up their calculator at the JH from 8:00 am - 12:00 pm.

HS- all students will pick up their calculators at the high school from 8:00 am - 12:00 pm.

Students do not need to request or complete a form before receiving the calculator. A form will be completed at the time of pick up. If the student did not turn in a calculator last year, they will not be issued a new calculator.

Sweeny ISD
May 26 at 4:07 PM ·

Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer (P-EBT) is a one-time food benefit for families who lost access to free or reduced-price meals due to school closures. Eligible P-EBT families will receive application instructions from schools in late May. The P-EBT application will open the first week of June.

P-EBT food benefits are for children who received SNAP food benefits for March 2020 and children who are certified for free or reduced-price school meals during the 2019-20 Texas school year. For more information, visit: hhs.texas.gov/PEBT

Reminder: please make plans to pick-up and drop-off any remaining student items (all grade levels) today from 3:00 to 6:00 pm, at Sweeny Elementary School. post_text:
It’s looking a lot like graduation at Sweeny High School! Before the celebration begins, we would like to express our gratitude for those that have helped us in making it all possible. Our maintenance team has done an awesome job of preparing the stadium and setting up the seats and stages. Our custodians have taken extra steps to ensure that our facilities are ready for our families.

Thank you to Pastor BJ McCurdy and his team from New Shores Church for donating their time and equipment for our live feed. Thank you to Phillip Nelson from Pro Visuals for filming graduation for all students to view at a later time. We also appreciate our staff members who will serve as ushers for the ceremony.

We are looking forward to the Class of 2020 graduation ceremony with our Seniors on Friday, May 29th at 8:00 pm. All guests must have a ticket. Please join us for the live feed on the Sweeny ISD Facebook page.

post_text:
Congratulations to Andrew Hillman, a 5th grade student at Sweeny Elementary. Andrew has been selected as this year's winner of the TXSSAR's Annual Americanism Elementary School Poster Contest. As the Texas Society, 1st Place Winner, Andrew will receive a cash award of $300. Additionally, his poster titled “Valley Forge”, will be "sponsored" at the National Society's Annual Congress (Richmond, Virginia July 10 - 15, 2020) where it will be judged with other State Societies' entries.

For a full list of contests sponsored by the National Society of the Sons of the American Revolution, visit their website https://www.cradletxsar.org/contests/. The contests are open to students in grades 3 - 12, and focus on the American Revolution and our "Founding Principles and Documents, and the Sacrifices that bind us as a Nation."

Members of the Bond Oversight Committee held a virtual meeting to review the progress of the construction at each campus and expenditures to date. The construction on the CTE facility at the high school started on January 6th. Many projects have been completed and everything is moving forward as scheduled. There has also been a tremendous amount of work accomplished and some critical planning and staging for the beginning of interior work at the Junior High and Elementary campuses. The Bond Oversight Committee will plan their next meeting for a date in June. For pictures and updates please see the District website.

This is a reminder that Sweeny ISD will begin serving the hot meal lunches tomorrow, Friday, April 24th from 11:30 a.m. to 1:00 p.m. at Sweeny High School. You will enter the bus lane near the tennis courts on Hackberry Street.

These meals are free to all children who live in our attendance zone ages zero to eighteen. Each meal will include lunch for the day, as well as, a breakfast for the next morning.

Based on State requirements, you will either need to:

Have your children with you in the car OR
Know your students lunch numbers OR
If your child is below school age, you will need to have their birth certificate

You will have to get out of your car in order to pick up your meals after your information has been verified by a school employee.

We will not be able to deliver meals, so all meals will have to be picked up.

We are grateful for your support and cooperation as we work together to keep Sweeny ISD safe.

In order to support our families, Sweeny ISD will restart the hot meal lunches beginning Friday, April 24th. The free meals will be provided to all children ages zero to eighteen who live in our attendance zone. The meals will include lunch for the day, as well as breakfast for the next morning.

Meals will be available for pickup Monday thru Friday from 11:30 a.m. - 1:00 p.m. at the High School. You will need to enter the bus lane near the tennis courts from Hackberry Street.

Based on State requirements, you will either need to:

1. Have your children with you in the car OR
2. Know your student's ID number (their lunch number) OR
3. If your child is below school age, have his/her birth certificate

You will have to get out of your car in order to pick up your meals after your information has been verified by a school employee.

We will not be able to deliver meals, so all meals will have to be picked up.

We are grateful for your support and cooperation as we work together to keep Sweeny ISD safe.

post_text:
As many of you are aware, Governor Greg Abbott has extended his executive order closing school facilities through the remainder of the year.

While this is not what we had hoped for, the safety and health of our students, parents, and community is top priority.

For those seniors graduating, we are working quickly to ensure we provide you with the best graduation possible. Expect a senior student and parent survey this afternoon. We will notify you as soon as your feedback is received and plans are finalized. We do not want to rush, but instead want make sure you have the celebration you deserve. We are extremely proud of you Class of 2020.

We will continue with our Sweeny Connected virtual learning. We are thankful for our teachers, students, and parents who have all transitioned into the new learning environment and continue to work hard in order to make sure our students do not get behind.

We are truly blessed to be a part of Sweeny ISD. Please continue to take care of yourselves and your family. We will get through this together. Please stay healthy and safe.

Since we have been away from school SHS student, Byron Randon, has written his own book titled Be Something Great. He is now challenging all SISD students to also write their own short story or book. We decided to take it a step further and make it a contest!!

1. We will have 3 categories: elementary, junior high and high school (you may enter individually or as a group of 2-3)
2. Email your story or take pictures of your story and send it to the elementary librarian, Mrs. Leopold at lleopold@sweenyisd.org (please make sure to include your name and grade)
3. Deadline to enter is Friday, April 24th
4. Winners will receive a gift card (either in the mail or when we return to school)
5. Have fun - this shouldn't be like homework and doesn't have to be too lengthy!!

post_text: Good Monday morning! We hope you all had a great Easter weekend. As students continue their virtual learning this week, we wanted to remind you about the resources we have available. Information for students and parents is posted on our website. If you have technology questions, you can reach out to us through email or by calling the help line. Please note that we have adjusted the hours of the help line to 10:00 am - 4:00 pm Monday - Friday. Thank you parents for your continued support and patience as we provide virtual instruction to our students.

post_text:
BE THE LIGHT - Tomorrow night we will turn on our Softball/Baseball complex lights from 8:00 p.m. – 9:00 p.m. as a symbol of hope, unity, and assurance.

We hope that you enjoy this video as it honors all those young men and women who would be playing under those lights if we were in school - especially this year’s seniors. We miss our students, parents, and community.

“Owning our story can be hard but not nearly as difficult as spending our lives running from it. Embracing our vulnerabilities is risky but not nearly as dangerous as giving up on love and belonging and joy—the experiences that make us the most vulnerable. Only when we are brave enough to explore the darkness will we discover the infinite power of our light.”

― Brene Brown

PLEASE SHARE SHARE SHARE ♥️

ATTENTION Sweeny ISD, community members, and surrounding communities:

MONDAY MARCH 30
10 a.m. - 2:30 p.m.
Stewart’s Parking Lot

**Age 16 and up and weigh at least 122 lbs

Sweeny National Honor Society had their spring blood drive rescheduled and would like to still do whatever possible to support the current emergency need of the Gulf Coast Regional Blood Center that serves our area and surrounding areas.

Please note they are following strict sanitary guidelines to keep each donor SAFE.

It is our goal to help address this great need with as many donations as possible. I have no doubt our community will help make this happen! #beablessing

PLEASE NOTE.....the CODE in the attached flyer and make an appointment ONLINE and you will be in and out very quickly♥️

Walk ups also welcome BUT we will just ask for you to stay in your vehicle until it’s your turn♥️

Thanks in advance for making a difference and saving lives!!

Please contact Christi Wesley if any questions.

**Thank you so much to Sweeny Stewart’s Grocery for help making this happen!!

Reminder: Meal information for Wednesday, March 18th

Sweeny ISD will continue to support our families by providing FREE meals to all children who live in our attendance zone ages 0 to 18.

Curbside Pick Up:
Sweeny Elementary cafeteria parking lot (11:30 am - 1:00 pm)
District staff will deliver food to the vehicle; families will not need to exit the vehicle to receive the meals.
Children must be present in the car to receive the meal.

Delivery:
Delivery provided by district staff (11:30 a.m. - 1:00 pm) Families will need to meet the staff outside.
Children must be present in order to receive the meal.

If you have previously filled out and submitted the form, there is no need to submit another one. If your children would like to participate in the curbside pick up or meal delivery please fill out the form by 8:00 a.m. the day of pickup or delivery.

post_text:
Thank you to SJH student,Kassidy Anderson, for leading the invocation at Tuesday night’s Board of Trustees meeting. Also, thank you to Mia Parra, Jay Johnson, and Aidan Garcia for leading the pledges.

The Board recognized and celebrated the accomplishments of the following students: Junior High Region Band members, High School Region and Area Band members, Junior High Students of the Month, and our High School Art students for their participation in the Houston Livestock Show and Rodeo Student Art Program.

Other highlights from the board meeting: National School Bus Driver Appreciation Week is February 10th – 14th, and our Board of Trustees appreciates our team of dedicated, hardworking bus drivers. Sweeny ISD CFO, Amy Carter, was recognized for her recent certification from the TASBO as a Certified Texas School Business Specialist. Elementary Librarian, Linda Leopold, received a grant from CPA’s Helping Schools, and James Melton was sworn in as our new Sweeny ISD police officer.

Due to Spring Break, the next Board of Trustees meeting will be Tuesday, March 17th at 7:00 pm.

shared_text:
Sweeny ISD
January 8 at 10:58 AM ·

The Sweeny ISD Walk of Honor Committee is currently seeking nominations. If you previously submitted a nomination, please consider resubmitting. Nominations are open until Monday, February 3rd, 2020.
Categories: Individuals may be nominated to represent one of three categories:

• Educator: Identified as – Administrator, Teacher, Activity Sponsor, Athletic Coach, Staff
• Alumni: Identified as – Graduate of any High School in the history of Sweeny ISD
• Supporter: Identified as – A Major Volunteer, Contributor or Sponsor who has supported Sweeny ISD in a capacity other than an Educator or Alumni

For more information, please visit the Walk of Honor page on the SISD website

post_text:
The 8th grade students visited the high school today to learn about the different CTE programs. The students were greeted by some of our band members and then welcomed by Dr. Hill, Principal Mader, freshman counselor Mrs. Kersh, and CTE Coordinator Mr. Manley. The students then traveled to the CTE classes to hear more about the programs. They also had the opportunity to visit with students about the various clubs and organizations they could join.

While the CTE teachers were presenting to the 8th graders, their classes attended our first Career Conversations event. Students met with industry professionals to gain real world insight about the education and experience needed for their careers. Thank you to all who volunteered their time to educating our youth and positively impacting their career journey.

post_text:
Over the Christmas break, prep work began on the CTE building with asbestos abatement and the placement of a temporary wall to block off the main building. Welding equipment for the dual credit welding class was moved to a new temporary location in Sweeny. This will allow our students to continue their classes without having to travel to the college. Other projects that were completed were the resurfacing of the tennis courts in preparation for their season, and an issue with the roof at the high school from the previous remodel was fixed.

The public is invited to attend the next Bond Oversight Committee Meeting that will be held on January 23rd at 6:00 pm.

post_text:
During the regular board meeting on Tuesday, December 10, 2019, the Sweeny ISD Board of Trustees approved the appointment of Denise Papillion as the new Sweeny ISD Elementary Principal.

She grew up in Raywood, Texas and is excited to be back in a small, close knit community. Papillion has served as Assistant Principal and Coordinator of Curriculum and Instruction for Angleton ISD. She served as a classroom teacher and Curriculum Instructional Specialist in Goose Creek CISD. She earned her bachelor’s degree from Lamar University and her master’s degree from the University of Houston-Clear Lake.

“I look forward to being part of the pride and traditions of Sweeny Elementary. My focus is on building relationships with the students, staff and families. Together we will allow each and every child to reach his/her true potential.”

Papillion will begin work as SISD Elementary Principal on January 6, 2020.

She earned her bachelor’s degree from Lamar University and her master’s degree from the University of Houston-Clear Lake.

post_text:
Coca Cola Southwest Beverages has partnered with local retailers and schools to donate Powerade football sideline equipment to local area High School Football Teams.

Coca Cola Southwest Beverages launched a Fall Football program in 2019, partnering Powerade with local retailers and schools. The schools that participated out of the El Campo facility were El Campo High School, Sweeny High School, Palacios High School, Wharton High School, and Faith Family H.S. Victoria.

Local Football themed displays were put up in area retailers- Walmart, Brookshire Brothers, Lowes, and Stewart’s. A drawing was held out of the South East Market unit that includes Houston, Beaumont, Bryan, Nacogdoches, Conroe, and El Campo. El Campo Coca- Cola and the winning store, Stewart’s in Sweeny, presented a check for $1,500 to Sweeny High School to benefit several groups.

The program's goal is to encourage active lifestyles through the support of school programs.

post_text:
This weekend 16 Sweeny students will be participating in the Region 13 choir. Participation in this group is earned in blind auditions and is a high honor in choral music.

Representing Sweeny Junior High will be: Alyssa Alaniz, Jayla Archie, Laura Casas, Mia Huffman, Rhiley Larsen, Severin Moers, Allyson Nichols, Aleila Velazquez, Luke Hobill, Cody Holesovsky, and Brooklyn Behrend.

Sweeny High School will be represented by: Cody Morris, first chair bass, Shelby Dike, second chair alto, Kaitlyn Fields, third chair alto, Ashlon Williams, fourth chair alto, and Justin Dodson, first chair tenor.

A former Sweeny Choral Director, Perry Dean will conduct the high school choir. The Junior High choir will be accompanied by Drusilla Vinson, Sweeny’s current choral teacher.

The concert will be held at Bay City High School on Saturday, November 16th at 4:00 pm.

post_text: Sweeny ISD is entering phase 2 of our Hotspot Initiative which provides free WiFi to our students and their families. We would like to extend the offer to families of students at Sweeny Elementary to opt-in to check out a Hotspot for the school year. If your family would benefit from this service, please check your email and fill out the form by Friday, November 15. Once you have filled out the form, you will be contacted with a link to a user agreement that you will need to complete. Once the agreement is returned, your child will have a device distributed to them at school that they may bring home.

post_text: Thank you for a great marching season!
shared_text:
Sweeny ISD Band
October 19, 2019 at 7:08 PM ·

The Sweeny High School Marching Band had their final competitive performance of the season this afternoon in Ganado, Texas. All the students performed well, and the band received an Excellent rating.

We are so thankful to our students for all the hard work, time, and dedication they gave this season’s Superspy show. We’d also like to thank all of the amazing band parents, administration, community members, clinicians, and more than anything our junior high Band Aids for all of their support for these outstanding kids. This band could not exist without everyone’s help.

Now let’s finish out this football season! #SweenyPride
